in the MaxWell Daily Club will include ways to develop your practice further. </p>',1,'2008-10-15 19:41:04','2009-02-06 00:09:20',NULL),(23,23,'','<p>Strive to carve out time for quiet reflection every day, even if it can only be 15 minutes when your schedule is harried. A daily ritual for contemplation and stillness is a very grounding practice, which you need in your busy life. Whether you follow specific rituals and instructions or have created your own method, there is overwhelming evidence showing that your daily practice results in a healthier and happier life. </p>\r\n<p>One way to enhance your dedication to a daily practice: Explore new rituals and concepts that help you stay mindfully engaged. The Personalized Plan you receive when you join the MaxWell Daily Club will include specific ideas for developing your practice further.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 19:47:10','2009-02-06 00:09:59',NULL),(24,24,'','<p>Experiment with carving out a little time for mindfulness. If your schedule is packed, you might need to start with just once a week. You&rsquo;ll notice that the ritual contributes to your sense of connection and wellbeing. When you are most busy, you may find you benefit from the serenity more than ever. </p>\r\n<p>Whether you follow specific rituals and instructions or have created your own method, there is overwhelming evidence showing that your daily practice results in a healthier and happier life. To help you stay mindfully engaged, try on different approaches to see what feels most comfortable. The Personalized Plan you receive when you join the MaxWell Daily Club will include specific ideas for developing your practice further.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 19:48:01','2009-02-06 00:11:29',NULL),(25,25,'','<p>People like you who have strong faith often cite it as an important part of their lives. Faith can provide a guiding principle that shapes your experiences with the world around you and your relationships with others.</p>\r\n<p>The concept of God, spirit guides, or angels is not accepted by everyone, and even fewer people have true faith in these aspects of the divine. There are times when differences of faith are used as a cause for conflict. Consider the elements of your faith to explore how well they serve you and others.</p>\r\n<p>MaxWell Daily Club members: Check your Personalized Plan for suggestions on nourishing your faith.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 19:52:08','2009-02-06 00:12:21',NULL),(26,26,'','<p>Even if it&rsquo;s accompanied by some uncertainty, your openness to the concept of God, spirit guides, or angels provides a good foundation for developing spiritual wellbeing, if you choose to delve deeper.&nbsp; Not everyone accepts these aspects of the divine, and true faith is even more rare. </p>\r\n<p>Your personal choice pertaining to faith and spirituality cannot be judged, and you may choose to retain your reservations.&nbsp; However, it might be worth considering the elements of your spirituality to see how well they serve you and others. In this way, perhaps you can become more certain, one way or the other.</p>\r\n<p>MaxWell Daily Club members: Check your Personalized Plan for suggestions for exploring spirituality.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 19:52:47','2009-02-06 00:12:51',NULL),(27,27,'','<p>Your response indicates that you don&rsquo;t see convincing evidence for the existence of God, spirit guides, or angels. Some people are willing to accept these aspects of the divine, but far fewer have true faith. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Your personal choice pertaining to faith and spirituality cannot be judged, and you may choose to retain your reservations.&nbsp; However, it might be worth exploring how you developed your views and giving them a fresh look. You may find your opinions were engrained at an early age and have shifted over time to allow for new beliefs.&nbsp; For many, finding a personally fulfilling spiritual practice brings greater health and peace.</p>\r\n<p>MaxWell Daily Club members: Check your Personalized Plan for suggestions for exploring your spirituality.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:01:42','2009-02-06 00:13:31',NULL),(28,28,'','<p>You have a special gift: Having the capacity to identify the blessings in your life. Every life has challenges, but your ability to appreciate your blessings means that to some extent you can make meaning out of pain. You possess an important tool in seeking the silver lining in experiences that are difficult. And you cultivate your spiritual wellbeing by spending time focusing on the positive. </p>\r\n<p>For MaxWell Daily Club members, your Personalized Plan will include ways to enhance your optimism even more.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:02:15','2009-02-06 00:14:07',NULL),(29,29,'','<p>If your life has an ample dose of challenges, it can be difficult to see the positive. However, when you look closely, you occasionally discover the silver lining in the problems you face. The more you can learn to appreciate your blessings, the more you will develop the ability to make meaning out of pain. Keep working on it, and you might find that it becomes easier to identify more blessings and thus feel more blessed.</p>\r\n<p>For MaxWell Daily Club members, your Personalized Plan will include techniques to accentuate the positive experiences in your life. </p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:02:36','2009-02-06 00:14:28',NULL),(30,30,'','<p>If your life has an ample dose of challenges, it can be difficult to see the positive. The more you can learn to appreciate your blessings, the more you will develop the ability to make meaning out of pain. Keep working on finding the silver lining in the problems you face, and you might find that it becomes easier to identify more blessings&mdash;and thus feel more blessed. It is worth the effort to try this out, as it might help you see more beauty around you, and will be uplifting.</p>\r\n<p>For MaxWell Daily Club members, your Personalized Plan will include techniques to accentuate the positive experiences in your life. </p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:03:20','2009-02-06 00:14:52',NULL),(31,31,'','<p>Your confidence and flexibility requires considerable faith and trust that things will work out. And you should feel very good about yourself, as this is not always easy to do. </p>\r\n<p>Continue to cultivate the ability to stay in this flow state and place of joy, even when life strikes a period that is more challenging. When those times do come, your comfort with the varied nature of life will help you remain liberated from the traps along the way. </p>\r\n<p>The Personalized Plan that comes with your MaxWell Daily Club membership will have ideas for helping you maintain and perhaps increase your sense of ease. </p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:03:40','2009-02-06 00:15:46',NULL),(32,32,'','<p>It feels good when you can achieve a state of peace, finding the faith and trust that things will work out. Consider the circumstances under which you can release your attachment and embrace uncertainty compared to the different situations when you cannot. If you can identify common themes, you might be able to find a way to cultivate more of your free spirit, which in general, allows us to experience more joy in our lives.</p>\r\n<p>The Personalized Plan that comes with your MaxWell Daily Club membership will have ideas for achieving comfort with the ups and downs in life to increase your sense of ease.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:04:11','2009-02-06 00:16:12',NULL),(33,33,'','<p>It may be important for you to find ways to cultivate more of your free spirit. Discomfort with uncertainty can be draining because life is generally unpredictable. Yet it requires considerable faith and trust to believe that things will work out, especially if you have suffered in the past. </p>\r\n<p>You might look more closely at those rare times when you have been able to go with the flow. Seek a common theme that provides you with some insight so that you can develop this capacity further, which will allow you to experience more joy in your life. </p>\r\n<p>The Personalized Plan that comes with your MaxWell Daily Club membership will have ideas for achieving comfort with the ups and downs. </p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:08:06','2009-02-06 00:16:37',NULL),(34,34,'','<p>Congratulations on making time to cultivate your life outside of work. Without adequate rest, particularly detachment from technology, it&rsquo;s easy to lose sight of your connection to others and how much it contributes to your wellbeing and happiness. As you may realize, the pace of modern society can be blamed for many of the ailments and illnesses people face. Your ability to unplug is an important habit.</p>\r\n<p>As you may already realize, it is important to protect this practice vigilantly when demands of career, finances, or others&rsquo; expectations threaten to consume your regular day of rest. And remember to occasionally recreate the rituals of the day to keep it fresh and fun.</p>\r\n<p>MaxWell Daily Club members will find restorative practices outlined in the Personalized Plan.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:08:29','2009-02-09 07:07:33',NULL),(35,35,'','<p>The pace of modern society can be blamed for many of the ailments and illnesses people face. Your long-term wellbeing and happiness may depend on your ability to cultivate time away from work, despite the demands of career, finances, and others&rsquo; expectations. Ideally, strive to unplug on a weekly basis. </p>\r\n<p>Without adequate rest, particularly detachment from technology, you can lose sight of your connection to others and how much they contribute to the richness of life. To keep it fun, consider creating interesting rituals and activities, special meals, and gatherings, away from the hustle and bustle of the daily chores and &ldquo;noise&rdquo; in your life.</p>\r\n<p>MaxWell Daily Club members will discover ideas for restorative practices in the Personalized Plan.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:08:51','2009-02-06 00:18:00',NULL),(36,36,'','<p>It&rsquo;s not unusual to get swept up in the pace of modern society, but unfortunately it can be blamed for many of the ailments and illnesses people face. Without adequate rest, particularly detachment from technology, it&rsquo;s easy to lose sight of your connection to others and how much that contributes to your well-being and happiness. </p>\r\n<p>The demands of career, finances, and others&rsquo; expectations may make a weekly break seem impossible. In that case, start off by trying it once or twice. Spend time away from the hustle and bustle and you may find your productivity increases and you can unplug more often.</p>\r\n<p>MaxWell Daily Club members will find strategies outlined in the Personalized Plan.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:09:19','2009-02-06 00:18:26',NULL),(37,45,'','<p>Your sense that life has real meaning is wonderful&mdash;and essential to your health and happiness. Given that you see a clear focus, be on the lookout for obstacles to fulfilling your life&rsquo;s purpose lurking in your behavior, work, problematic relationships, or other areas. At the same time, watch for evidence that your restrictions may be too rigid and you need to re-evaluate your plans or timeframe. While not easy to do, making changes that keep you on target can lead to a deeper more authentic existence. </p>\r\n<p>As a MaxWell Daily Club member, you&rsquo;ll receive a Personalized Plan with more ideas about achieving your purpose in life. </p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:11:50','2009-02-06 00:19:16',NULL),(38,37,'','<p>While your life has meaning, you may not always be able to see it clearly. Developing a stronger sense of your innate worth and value is essential for your health and happiness. And when you are focused, be on the lookout for obstacles in your behavior, work, maintaining problematic relationships, and other areas. Sometimes it&rsquo;s necessary to make significant changes in order to stay on track. While not easy to do, the reward is a deeper more authentic existence.</p>\r\n<p>As a MaxWell Daily Club member, you&rsquo;ll receive a Personalized Plan with ideas about clarifying and achieving your purpose in life.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:13:23','2009-02-09 04:26:24',NULL),(39,38,'','<p>Developing an innate sense of worth and value is essential for your health and happiness. Whatever obstacles are obstructing your focus&mdash;your own behavior, work, problematic relationships, or other issues&mdash;your lack of purpose leaves you a little lost. Be on the lookout for a sense that your actions or the demands placed upon you are at odds with your intrinsic sense of what feels right. These are the areas you must evaluate to find the changes that will guide you toward a more authentic experience.</p>\r\n<p>As a MaxWell Daily Club member, you&rsquo;ll receive a Personalized Plan with guidance for clarifying and achieving your purpose in life.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:13:46','2009-02-09 07:07:47',NULL),(40,39,'','<p>Having developed a range of intimate interactions, you&rsquo;re on the path to stay well balanced and happy.&nbsp; Intimacy is one of the key experiences that adds meaning to life. For most, the assumption is that intimacy and sex are one and the same. You know there&rsquo;s more to it. You respect yourself enough to feel comfortable sharing deeper parts of yourself and your feelings with others, bringing you closer together. This ability is the ultimate antidote for loneliness.</p>\r\n<p>Your Personalized Plan includes several options for exploring deeper intimacy. Become a MaxWell Daily Club member for access.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:14:19','2009-02-06 00:21:52',NULL),(41,40,'','<p>Unlike many, you know that sex and intimacy are not the same. Having developed a range of intimate interactions, you&rsquo;re on the path to stay well balanced and happy. But perhaps you sometimes feel vulnerable and are not comfortable sharing deeper parts of yourself. Ironically, your wariness can keep you apart and contribute to feelings of loneliness and isolation at times. </p>\r\n<p>Engage in some thought about how to develop greater comfort with closeness. Often, traumatic relationships from the past are at the root. Explore how you might safely examine the issues and work through them.</p>\r\n<p>Your Personalized Plan includes suggestions for developing deeper intimacy. Become a MaxWell Daily Club member for access.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:14:36','2009-02-06 00:22:23',NULL),(42,41,'','<p>Whether you believe that intimacy and sex are one and the same, or you avoid both, you are missing out on a deep connection that adds meaning to life. Perhaps you feel vulnerable and are not comfortable sharing deeper parts of yourself and your feelings with others. Ironically, this barrier keeps you apart, contributing to feelings of loneliness and isolation. </p>\r\n<p>Engage in some thought about how to develop greater comfort with closeness. Often, traumatic relationships from the past are at the root. Explore how you might safely examine the issues and work through them.</p>\r\n<p>Your Personalized Plan includes suggestions for developing deeper intimacy. Become a MaxWell Daily Club member for access.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:15:29','2009-02-06 00:23:07',NULL),(43,42,'','<p>Perhaps you are blessed in loving deeply and not having suffered a significant loss. If that&rsquo;s the case, explore your feelings about the disruptions in life such as sickness, job changes, or moving. But if your lack of grief comes from insulating yourself from the dangers of deep love, you are limiting your ability to experience joy. The suffering you experience from the grief of loneliness can bring intense sadness. Consider small forays into caring, such as volunteering opportunities, getting a pet, or just tending a garden.</p>\r\n<p>The Personalized Plan that comes with your MaxWell Daily Club membership will have more ideas for learning to love and coping with grief effectively.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:23:17','2009-02-06 00:26:09',NULL),(44,43,'','<p>The experience of grief is deeply personal, and yours may share few similarities with others&rsquo; except that you have had the courage to love and accept your loss. That alone means you&rsquo;re in better shape than many. </p>\r\n<p>Interestingly, grief is not static and often will return. Be mindful if sudden sadness arises, or feelings of loneliness and isolation appear. They may be a call to action. Allow yourself to fully experience these feelings as an important part of staying well balanced and healthy&mdash;and the most sure way of moving through dark periods.</p>\r\n<p>The Personalized Plan that comes with your MaxWell Daily Club membership will have more ideas for coping with grief.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:23:39','2009-02-06 00:26:57',NULL),(45,44,'','<p>It takes time to fully process grief and courage to accept our losses. You may hold onto memories as a tangible expression of your lost love one, which is poignant and difficult to endure. </p>\r\n<p>When sadness and loneliness grip you, allow yourself to fully experience these feelings, which is an important part of staying healthy and balanced&mdash;and the most sure way of moving through dark periods.</p>\r\n<p>Over time you will find that grief will ebb and flow. By staying mindful, you will begin to see how you are moving through the process. In this way, you may find a path to greater solace. </p>\r\n<p>The Personalized Plan that comes with your MaxWell Daily Club membership will have more ideas for recovering from grief.</p>',1,'2008-10-15 20:24:03','2009-02-06 00:27:31',NULL),(46,46,NULL,'This is important and useful. It may take a while to develop them, but many of us can clearly identify specific goals in our lives, whether they be personal, professional or both. As these create a target for our efforts, stating that you have them suggests that you are set up well to maintain your focus and have a useful barometer to assess your progress. It is important to remember, however, that over time goals may change, and thus it is also important not to become too rigid. \n ',1,'2008-10-23 21:21:30','2008-10-23 21:21:30',NULL),(47,47,NULL,'Having specific goals in your personal and professional life can be very useful. For one, they help us to maintain focus. Also, having goals provides us with an opportunity to assess our progress along the way. Developing more clarity in your goals will help you in both of these respects and guide you in making decision. It is important to remember, however, that over time goals may change, and thus it is important not to become too rigid. ',1,'2008-10-23 21:21:53','2008-10-23 21:21:53',NULL),(48,48,NULL,'Having specific goals in your personal and professional life can be very useful. For one, they help us to maintain focus. Also, having goals provides us with an opportunity to assess our progress along the way. Developing goals will help you in both of these respects and guide you in making decision. If you cannot envision the long term that it may be easier to think closer in and identify short term goals that seem realistic for you to achieve in the near future.',1,'2008-10-23 21:22:18','2008-10-23 21:22:18',NULL),(49,49,NULL,'The ability to concentrate is a functional measure of a fairly intact life. Think about it, if you were in chronic pain, or particularly stressed out, it would be very difficult to do. The fact that you can concentrate for extended periods of time suggests that you are \"intact\" as a whole. While there may be opportunities for improvement, this is a very good place to be. Maintaining our mental faculties is something that many of us think about often and may even be concerned about. Thus, the key for you might be to develop those practices which maximize your \"brain function\".',1,'2008-10-23 21:28:06','2008-10-23 21:30:50',NULL),(50,50,NULL,'The ability to concentrate is a functional measure of a fairly intact life. Think about it, if you were in chronic pain, or particularly stressed out, it would be very difficult to do. Since this is not something you can do consistently, there is room for improvement. There are many things that could potentially help you and it would make sense to consider any and all of them, as  maintaining our mental faculties is something that many of us think about often and may even be concerned about. Thus, the key for you might be to develop those practices which maximize your \"brain function\".',1,'2008-10-23 21:29:01','2008-10-23 21:31:08',NULL),(51,51,NULL,'This may be something to work on. The ability to concentrate is a functional measure of a fairly intact life. Think about it, if you were in chronic pain, or particularly stressed out, it would be very difficult to do. Since this is not something you can do easily, there is a lot of room for improvement. There are many things that could potentially help you and it would make sense to consider any and all of them, as  maintaining our mental faculties is something that many of us think about often and may even be concerned about. Thus, the key for you might be to develop those practices which maximize your \"brain function\".',1,'2008-10-23 21:29:27','2008-10-23 21:31:18',NULL),(52,52,NULL,'Good. It is important for in considering our health, particularly our state of balance, to realize that \"rigidity\" is a condition that makes us more brittle and susceptible to ailments and problems of all sorts. Thus, having the ability to adapt to circumstances is essential. In that regard, often we must confront ourselves and our old views of our lives and living and move in new directions. Occasionally, we may need to check ourselves to ensure we do not hold onto things too tightly or longer than necessary.',1,'2008-10-23 21:30:21','2008-10-23 21:30:21',NULL),(53,53,NULL,' It is important for us in considering our health, particularly our state of balance, to realize that \"rigidity\" is a condition that makes us more brittle and susceptible to ailments and problems of all sorts. Thus, having the ability to adapt to circumstances is essential. In that regard, often we must confront ourselves and our old views of our lives and living and move in new directions. Your response suggests that you do have some capacity to do this, but that it might be difficult at other times. It becomes important, then, to find a way to ensure you do not hold onto things too tightly or longer than necessary. There are many practices that can cultivate this ability, they may be worth trying. \n',1,'2008-10-23 21:31:47','2008-10-23 21:34:59',NULL),(54,54,NULL,'It is important for us in considering our health, particularly our state of balance, to realize that \"rigidity\" is a condition that makes us more brittle and susceptible to ailments and problems of all sorts. Thus, having the ability to adapt to circumstances is essential. In that regard, often we must confront ourselves and our old views of our lives and living and move in new directions. Your response suggests that this is hard for you. It becomes important, then, to find a way to ensure you do not hold onto things too tightly or longer than necessary. There are many practices that can cultivate this ability, they may be worth trying, and they might offer you great relief in many respects.',1,'2008-10-23 21:32:26','2008-10-23 21:32:26',NULL),(55,55,NULL,'People are usually optimistic by nature, and this is generally a good way to be. There is a lot of medical research to suggest that those who are essentially optimistic do better when confronting challenging physical conditions. And, it also makes sense that this \"attitude\" improves our mental outlook and allows us to deal with life',1,'2008-10-23 21:33:14','2008-10-23 21:35:34',NULL),(56,56,NULL,'There is a lot of medical research to suggest that those who are essentially optimistic do better when confronting challenging physical conditions. And, it also makes sense that this \"attitude\" improves our mental outlook and allows us to deal with life',1,'2008-10-23 21:36:31','2008-10-23 21:36:31',NULL),(57,57,NULL,'Clearly, optimism is not something that can be simply turned on or off. However, there are ways to cultivate a more positive attitude and this may be important for you. There is a lot of medical research to suggest that those who are essentially optimistic do better when confronting challenging physical conditions. And, it also makes sense that this ',1,'2008-10-23 21:36:57','2008-10-23 21:36:57',NULL),(58,58,NULL,'Your answer suggests that you grow from difficult experiences. This ultimately suggests that you are able to find meaning in life',1,'2008-10-23 21:37:15','2008-10-23 21:37:15',NULL),(59,59,NULL,'It is not always easy to find meaning in life',1,'2008-10-23 21:37:35','2008-10-23 21:37:35',NULL),(60,60,NULL,'It is not always easy to find meaning in life',1,'2008-10-23 21:38:00','2008-10-23 21:38:00',NULL),(61,61,NULL,'It takes great emotional reserve to fully experience painful experiences without breaking down. Not many people can do this easily, so this is one of your strengths. Another question to ask is when you do experience these feelings, do they get stuck, or do they move through you and out of you so that you do not linger in the pain. Working with the emotions, so that they do not become \"destructive\" is another skill that often takes some work to master. ',1,'2008-10-23 21:38:36','2008-10-23 21:38:36',NULL),(62,62,NULL,'It takes great emotional reserve to fully experience painful experiences without breaking down. Not many people can do this easily, and it seems that this is hard for you at times. The other question to ask is when you do experience these feelings, do they get stuck, or do they move through you and out of you so that you do not linger in the pain. Working with the emotions, so that they do not become \"destructive\" is a skill that often takes some work to master.',1,'2008-10-23 21:39:06','2008-10-23 21:39:06',NULL),(63,63,NULL,'It takes great emotional reserve to fully experience painful experiences without breaking down. Not many people can do this easily, and it seems that this is hard for you to do. In all likelihood you are a very sensitive person. In some respects this is very nice; however, it also can make you vulnerable if you get stuck in your feelings. Working with the emotions, so that they do not become \"destructive\" is a skill that often takes some work to master. You might consider working with someone who can guide you in some techniques. A simple practice is to keep a journal and let the \"emotions\" come out, at least on paper.',1,'2008-10-23 21:39:43','2008-10-23 21:39:43',NULL),(64,64,NULL,'This is very important. Life in our modern world can be chaotic and overwhelming. It remains essential that we remove ourselves from the busy and serious environments we inhabit most of the time and find peace in those places and in those ways that provide us with relief. A regular practice, e.g. a weekly ritual can be particularly useful.',1,'2008-10-23 21:40:03','2008-10-23 21:40:03',NULL),(65,65,NULL,'Life in our modern world can be chaotic and overwhelming. It remains essential that we remove ourselves from the busy and serious environments we inhabit most of the time and find peace in those places and in those ways that provide us with relief. While you can do this on occasion, a regular practice, e.g. a weekly ritual, going to the beach or a nearby park or lake to take a hike, may be particularly useful for you. ',1,'2008-10-23 21:40:25','2008-10-23 21:40:25',NULL),(66,66,NULL,'Life in our modern world can be chaotic and overwhelming. It remains essential that we remove ourselves from the busy and serious environments we inhabit most of the time and find peace in those places and in those ways that provide us with relief. Without this, \"debris\" often piles up and creates many types of imbalance, from chronic ailments to depression. A regular practice, e.g. a weekly ritual, going to the beach or a nearby park or lake to take a hike, may be a particularly good way to begin to address our need to relax and play. ',1,'2008-10-23 21:40:57','2008-10-23 21:40:57',NULL),(67,67,NULL,'This is not always easy and suggests you are thoughtful and have good self esteem. In a world where cooperation is essential, there is a great need for people like you, who can work with others and make mutual decisions, without always ',1,'2008-10-23 21:41:34','2008-10-23 21:41:34',NULL),(68,68,NULL,'In a world where cooperation is essential, confrontations often begin when people feel they need to take control and be right. While this is sometimes necessary, a skill to develop is one that allows us to work with others to make mutual decisions. Since this is something you can occasionally do, you are in a position to see the difference between those circumstances that allow you to remain relaxed and those that do not. Often any weakness in our self esteem creates a sense that if we are not careful, e.g. in control, that others will take advantage of us. The implications of this go further than the decisions themselves and can have other health consequences. For this reason it is important to examine the nature of your need for control to the extent that it exists.',1,'2008-10-23 21:41:55','2008-10-23 21:41:55',NULL),(69,69,NULL,'In a world where cooperation is essential, confrontations often begin when people feel they need to take control and be right. While this is sometimes necessary, a skill to develop is one that allows us to work with others to make mutual decisions. Often any weakness in our self esteem creates a sense that if we are not careful, e.g. in control, that others will take advantage of us. The implications of this go further than the decisions themselves and can have other health consequences. For this reason it is important to examine the nature of your need for control.',1,'2008-10-23 21:42:11','2008-10-23 21:42:11',NULL),(71,NULL,'This is an answer','Hello.  I\'m an answer.  You\'re a reject.',0,'2008-11-13 21:47:10'