INSERT INTO `quiz_recommendations` VALUES (1,1,'Fair, but small changes can make a difference','<p>Your body presents some challenges for you, but the good news is that small changes can bring big rewards to your physical health. You&rsquo;ve probably tried a number of approaches to improve your body&rsquo;s appearance and performance. Don&rsquo;t be discouraged. Most people can&rsquo;t keep up overly restrictive diets or habits. But there are ways to feel good and get healthier at the same time.</p>\r\n<p><b> Try these ideas to improve your physical wellbeing:</b></p>\r\n<p>1. You need to care for your health and looks with healthy habits. The first step, though, is to get into the right frame of mind to follow through with any plan. Talk through with a close friend any emotional issues that are holding you back, to make it easier to take good care of yourself physically.</p>\r\n<p>2. One tip that may make it easier to treat your body well: Get adequate sleep. Good quality sleep is essential for optimal health, mental acuity, and emotional balance. And recent research links inadequate sleep with weight gain, diabetes, heart disease, and high blood pressure.  If you don&rsquo;t leave enough time for sleep, consider making it a priority. But if sleep difficulties or your busy life are ruining your rest, there are solutions. Start by designating a set bedtime and a wind-down routine for the last two hours of your evening. Check your bedroom environment for light and noise. Also, avoid upsetting conversations and activities such as watching &ldquo;bad news&rdquo; right before you go to sleep.</p>\r\n<p>3. You don&rsquo;t have to feel tired. A balance of nutrition, physical fitness, and rest can help make your body more efficient. For example, physical activity generates more energy by improving muscle tone and flexibility as well as how your body uses oxygen; it&rsquo;s great for your mind too! Be sure to start slowly so you stay safe and maintain your enthusiasm.</p>\r\n<p>4. Next, you need a healthy eating plan that provides plenty of energy and nutrients to keep your body and mind feeling good. Eating more nutritious foods (and fewer heavily processed or fat-laden ones) will give you more energy, strengthen your immune system, and help prevent diseases. To improve your regularity, slowly increase the amount of fiber-filled foods (vegetables, fruits, etc.) you eat, and cut back on processed and refined foods (bread, cakes, pasta) and animal products. Also, be sure to drink adequate fluids, especially water. Any level of dehydration can cause constipation. And if you&rsquo;re not active, getting your body moving will help keep your digestion moving.</p>\r\n<p>5. Reduce stress by addressing issues in your environment. An unpleasant environment can be a cause of stress, but gazing on an attractive sight can be restorative and inspiring. Seek to make your space comfortable and pleasing. Bring plants or flowers into your home, clear away clutter, and then take time to appreciate the beauty around you every day.</p>',675,849,1,'2008-10-08 22:11:19','2010-10-16 21:01:29',NULL),(2,1,'You are in good shape and can get to the next level','<p>You&rsquo;re in fairly good shape, but you realize your physical health could be even better. Some of your habits are working well for you, so take care to continue those. At the same time, you could feel even better by identifying areas that are out of balance and taking steps to change them.</p>\r\n<p><b>Try these ideas to improve your physical well-being:</b></p>\r\n<p>1. Your energy level is a pretty good assessment of your general state of health and functional abilities. Better nutrition, physical fitness, and rest&mdash;all balanced correctly&mdash;can help make your body more efficient. Staying hydrated is also important for physical and mental performance.</p>\r\n<p>2. You need a balanced diet and a balanced life to keep your body and mind active and working well. Achieving these will give you more energy, strengthen your immune system, and help prevent diseases. To improve your regularity, slowly increase the amount of fiber-filled foods (vegetables, fruits, etc.) you eat, and cut back on processed and refined foods (bread, cakes, pasta) and animal products. Also, be sure to drink adequate fluids, especially water. Any level of dehydration can cause constipation. And if you&rsquo;re not active, getting your body moving will help keep your digestion moving.</p>\r\n<p>3. Even slight sleep problems are worth investigating so you can feel your best. Good quality sleep is essential for optimal health, mental acuity, and emotional balance. And recent research links inadequate sleep with weight gain, diabetes, heart disease, and high blood pressure.  If you don&rsquo;t leave enough time for sleep, consider making it a priority. If you have some bad nights, start by tracking how you spend the day and evening on bad nights versus good ones. In particular, look for clues in what you eat, how active you are, and how you spend your evening hours.</p>\r\n<p>4. Increase your appreciation for your surroundings, and you&rsquo;ll feel revitalized. It&rsquo;s essential to have a positive connection with your environment so you can feel a sense of restoration for your body, mind, and spirit. If you need to enhance the appeal of your surroundings, start with small, manageable changes&mdash;especially if you can do them yourself. The satisfaction of accomplishment adds to the sense of pleasure. Look for ideas in the principles of Feng Shui, the Chinese art of space organization. Plant some flower seeds in the spring. A garden is a great place to cultivate appreciation for your surroundings.</p>\r\n<p>5. Keep up the good work, and remain open to novel concepts that might bring even healthier days ahead. Try healing practices that combine physical, mental, and spiritual components, such as meditation. Also, explore how your emotions can have a positive or negative impact on how your body feels.</p>',850,1299,1,'2008-10-08 22:12:43','2010-10-16 21:01:56',NULL),(3,1,'Your effort is paying off, focus on your well-being','<p>Your efforts to stay in shape are paying off by keeping your body in excellent physical health. Keep up the good work. You also want to stay in touch with changes in your body and new ideas for improving your well-being even more. There may be a number of options you&rsquo;ve yet to explore that could enhance your energy, reduce the signs of aging, and help you develop health that includes balance in every aspect of your life.</p>\r\n<p><b>Try these ideas to improve your physical well-being:</b></p>\r\n<p>1. You&rsquo;re on an excellent track toward many years of continued health. Continue to maintain your healthy habits, and be on the lookout for ways to improve your well-being. Everyone can do more to live a healthier, happier life. For example, if you don&rsquo;t already set aside time in your busy schedule for a relaxation break, consider trying it.</p>\r\n<p>2. Even at this excellent starting point, you might be able to have more energy, no matter what your age. Better nutrition, physical fitness, and rest&mdash;all balanced correctly&mdash;can help make your body more efficient. Something simple like staying hydrated can be critical for your physical and mental performance.</p>\r\n<p>3. Whatever your eating habits, most of us can do a little better by learning more about healthy nutrition, addressing issues that cause us to eat poorly, or finding ways to be less rigid about eating perfectly. If you keep your weight down with less-than-ideal eating habits, you may compromise your health by missing nutrients your body needs.</p>\r\n<p>4. If you ever experience bouts of constipation, there may be easy fixes. Have you been eating enough fiber-filled foods like fruits and vegetables? Are you drinking enough, especially water? Do you get enough exercise?</p>\r\n<p>5. Recent research links inadequate sleep with weight gain, diabetes, heart disease, and high blood pressure. That&rsquo;s one reason getting enough sleep is an important healthy habit. It&rsquo;s also good for your mental acuity and emotional balance. If you don&rsquo;t get 7 to 8 hours of sleep most nights, look for ways to improve your sleep hygiene.</p>\r\n<p>6. Cultivate your connection to your environment by appreciating the beauty around you daily. Take on tasks to care for your home and neighborhood to increase your satisfaction.  If you don&rsquo;t already have a favorite spot, consider designating a personal sanctuary. It could be a park bench where you enjoy watching birds or a special chair where you curl up with a cup of tea. Pick a place you can go for instant calm, comfort, and revitalization, whenever you need it. Even just picturing it in your mind can help.</p>\r\n<p>7. Each of us tends to gravitate toward one sense or another, such as a preference for beautiful views or lovely music. Practice working with all the senses, one per weekday and a few on weekends.</p>',1300,1600,1,'2008-10-08 22:13:24','2010-10-16 21:02:15',NULL),(4,2,'Fair','<p>You have suffered or neglected your spiritual wellbeing, but the good news is that brighter days are ahead. Taking some simple steps are likely to propel you toward a more satisfying spiritual life, leading to better health and wellbeing, peace and comfort. </p>\r\n<p>Start with easy ways to bring meaning to your life by opening up to friends and family, carving out time to interact with others in a meaningful way. Listen to music and read literature that resonates with your sense of purpose. Select a living thing to nurture, and revel in the joy of watching it develop.</p>\r\n<p>Your Personalized Plan includes many more simple, sustainable steps you can take today to find joy in life. It also includes changes to implement over the coming weeks and months that deliver larger benefits. To receive your Personalized Plan, join the MaxWell Daily Club. As a member, you&rsquo;ll also get helpful interactive tools, one-on-one coaching, invitations to exclusive events, discounts, and more.</p>',800,999,1,'2008-10-15 21:58:55','2009-02-06 00:28:03',NULL),(5,2,'Good','<p>You live a life that has significance, but a stronger spiritual connection could bring you more joy. Clearly, several of your habits are working well, and the task now is to identify the areas that are out of balance and take initial steps to find better health and wellbeing, peace and comfort.</p>\r\n<p>Bring more meaning to your life by identifying relationships to cultivate in a meaningful way. Find opportunities that resonate with your sense of purpose. Select a living thing to nurture, and revel in the miracle of watching it develop.</p>\r\n<p>Your Personalized Plan includes many more simple, sustainable steps you can take today enhance your spiritual life. It also includes changes to implement over the coming weeks and months that deliver larger benefits. To receive your Personalized Plan, join the MaxWell Daily Club. As a member, you&rsquo;ll also get helpful interactive tools, one-on-one coaching, invitations to exclusive events, discounts, and more.</p>',1000,1399,1,'2008-10-15 21:59:24','2009-02-06 00:29:32',NULL),(6,2,'Excellent','<p>You have developed a strong spiritual engagement and experience in your life. The rewards are apparent in your sense of calmness and appreciation for the richness of your interactions and intimacy. Remain mindful of the shifts in your sense of comfort and peace that can come as a result of events close to home or even those halfway around the world. And never cease exploring new ways to enhance your sense of enlightenment. There is always a new idea or perspective that can expand your understanding and compassion.</p>\r\n<p>Your Personalized Plan offers a variety of suggestions to broaden your horizons toward increased peace and kindness. Join the MaxWell Daily Club for access to helpful interactive tools, one-on-one coaching, invitations to exclusive events, discounts, and more. </p>',1400,1600,1,'2008-10-15 22:02:15','2009-02-06 00:29:14',NULL),(7,3,'Excellent','<p>Based on your responses to the preceding questions, your emotional state appears to be EXCELLENT! This is a very good place to be, but you realize you might be even better. Clearly, you have many things working and the idea now is to identify those areas that are still somewhat out of balance and take some initial steps to make the necessary adjustments so that you can incrementally improve the quality of your life. In fact, if you would like to consider your health from a broader, more holistic perspective, consider answering one of the following two questions to gain further insight into how you might achieve a state of health and vitality that you desire.</p>',16,24,0,'2008-10-23 21:42:50','2010-03-13 18:43:40',NULL),(8,3,'Fair','Based on your responses to the preceding questions, your emotional state appears to be GOOD. This is a good place to be, but you realize you could be even better. Clearly, you have several things working and the idea now is to identify those areas that are still somewhat out of balance and take some initial steps to make the necessary adjustments so that you can incrementally improve the quality of your life. In fact, if you would like to consider your health from a broader, more holistic perspective, consider answering one of the following two questions to gain further insight into how you might achieve a state of health and vitality that you desire.',8,15,0,'2008-10-23 21:43:10','2008-10-23 21:43:10',NULL),(9,3,'Poor','Based on your responses to the preceding questions, your emotional state appears to be FAIR. The good news is that there is a lot of room for improvement. And, often, taking some simple steps can help you move from a fair state of emotional health to a good one. In addition, if you would like to consider your health from a broader, more holistic perspective, consider answering one of the following two questions to gain further insight into how you might achieve the state of health and vitality that you desire.',1,7,0,'2008-10-23 21:43:31','2008-10-23 21:52:24',NULL),(13,25,'Revenue Survey Demo Recommendation 1','<p>Revenue Survey Demo Recommendation 1</p>',0,50,1,'2009-07-20 19:03:24','2009-07-20 19:03:39',NULL),(18,29,'You are hip and bold','<p><b>Your style is modern, trendy and ultra-chic</b></p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;re hip and bold, on the lookout for the latest trends and ideas and never afraid to incorporate brand-new and cutting-edge pieces into your own home d&eacute;cor. You tend to favor clean lines, sleek looks and black and white jazzed up with splashes of vibrant color.</p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;re a connoisseur, selecting Retro pieces&mdash;a Nelson Ball Clock, a Noguchi coffee table or fine imitations that fit your budget&mdash;and placing them strategically throughout your home, alongside glass, Lucite and lacquered furniture. If it&rsquo;s hot on the market and goes with your Flokati rug and New Age Italian chandelier, it&rsquo;s for you.</p>\r\n<p>Your Top 5 Design Resources:</p>\r\n<p>1.    Want a spot-on copy for less and can live without the retro-grade signature? Check out New York&rsquo;s boutique Modernica and the hip national retailer Room &amp; Board.</p>\r\n<p>2.    If you&rsquo;re in hot pursuit of customized, coordinated and affordable mod-style furniture and accessories, check out Danish superstore BoConcept, which has showrooms around the country filled with clean and contemporary pieces (many in your favored black, white and gray).</p>\r\n<p>3.    Looking for even more cost-conscious chic? Explore the sleek modern picks at IKEA, where the perfect find could come in for less than $10.</p>\r\n<p>4.    Explore 1stdibs online for products bound to make you drool. Billed as &ldquo;the world\'s most searched market place for antique and mid-century modern furniture,&rdquo; you&rsquo;ll find exceptional quality pieces such as a set of eight Mies van der Rohe caned chairs, Vladimir Kagan&rsquo;s iconic high back barrel sofa and sleek armchairs by Gio Ponti.</p>\r\n<p>5.    If you want to wow, consider wall coverings by Maya Romanoff. Her designs are anything but dull: precious metals, jewel-colored, even bedazzled.</p>',1201,1400,1,'2010-02-18 16:07:20','2010-10-17 15:55:24',NULL),(19,29,'You want comfortable and it works','<p><b>Your style is eclectic and transitional</b></p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;re happiest in a home that embraces a variety of looks, one that is neither too classic nor too contemporary: you want comfortable. You have little interest in design that&rsquo;s completely traditional or formal (too stiff and stuffy) or entirely modern (too sparse and cold). Rather, you opt to blend several styles, choosing furniture and accessories based on what catches your eye. This d&eacute;cor diversity lets you display both your grandmother&rsquo;s blanket chest and your beloved Noguchi paper light without a care&mdash;it all works together.</p>\r\n<p>Your Top 5 Design Resources:</p>\r\n<p>1.    Eboniste.com is a style resource for those who are looking for modern pieces that aren&rsquo;t sterile, geared toward shoppers who seek &ldquo;eccentric basics&rdquo;&mdash;including furniture, lighting, and accessories with a global flair.</p>\r\n<p>2.    If your furniture and accessories bring in lots of color and design variation, keep walls neutral to make your pieces pop. Consider China White by Benjamin Moore or the deeper taupe of the company&rsquo;s Peaceful Breeze.</p>\r\n<p>3.    Looking to fill in some accessory gaps, such as a wall mirror or vase? Look for store chains &mdash; such as Crate &amp; Barrel and West Elm&mdash;that offer simple-style pieces that work well with any type of decor.</p>\r\n<p>4.    If you&rsquo;re looking to light up your life&mdash;and your home&mdash;check out the fixtures at Kichler Lighting, which offers a huge range of transitional pieces, including Mission-style and Country looks that work with all styles.</p>\r\n<p>5.    Revel in the unique designs for home and clothing from Tracy Porter, a mix of East and West that unites with richness and flair for a style that&rsquo;s simply fabulous.</p>',1401,1800,1,'2010-02-18 16:08:45','2010-10-20 12:01:52',NULL),(20,29,'Classic looks define your home','<p><b>Your style is traditional</b></p>\r\n<p>Classic looks define your home, with antiques, rich colors and elegance paving the way. You like your furniture and your draperies formal and prefer plenty of patterned elements for a refined aesthetic that works with your old-fashioned sensibilities. Chandeliers are cast iron, or better yet, Swarovski crystals and the Grandfather clocks chime on the hour. Your aim: to create a space that hearkens back to yesteryear, embodying grace and elegant ways.</p>\r\n<p>Your Top 5 Design Resources:</p>\r\n<p>1.    Pick up a copy of Great Traditional Style by Shelley Stewart or Signature Style: Creating Beautiful Interiors, edited by Linda Hallam for ideas on how to cultivate Old World style in your own home.</p>\r\n<p>2.    If you&rsquo;re on the prowl for antiques, visit Carl Moore Antiques, the Houston antiques emporium where two decades of experience shows in the selection of fine furniture, accessories, tapestries and artwork. The entire inventory is on their website, along with each item&rsquo;s description, period, circa date, dimensions and price&mdash;leaving little room for disappointment.</p>\r\n<p>3.    Look for reproductions of classics at budget prices from Home Decorators. You&rsquo;ll find hand-hooked rugs from India, stained glass lamps, and solid wood furnishings (check the descriptions to avoid composites) in Queen Anne and ornately carved styles. Check the Home Decorators Outlet for even better bargains on select pieces.</p>\r\n<p>4.    Ethan Allen&rsquo;s Estate line (www.ethanallen.com/lifestyle/estate) features charming and cultivated pieces based on the aesthetics of the American South and 18th-century American style.</p>\r\n<p>5.    Working on a budget? Consider going on a treasure hunt at local estate sales. Often, a high-quality piece is mixed in with the bric-a-brac and you can pick it up for a song. Check CraigsList for postings, and watch the local paper and bulletin boards around town.</p>',800,1200,1,'2010-02-18 16:10:37','2010-10-20 12:02:47',NULL),(21,30,'Easy Spender','<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'times new roman\', sans-serif; font-size: large; font-weight: 800; \">Results</span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-weight: 800; \">:&nbsp;</span></span><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><b><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">The Easy Spender</font></b></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">When it comes to</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;money, you&rsquo;re happy-go-lucky.&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Why settle for seats in the balcony when for only $40 more, you could be sitting front and center?&nbsp; Your joie-de-vivre style makes you fun to be around, but you might be frittering away more money than you have to.&nbsp; Here are five money wasters</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;to reconsider</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">:</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">1.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">A new car.&nbsp; That new car smell is wonderful, and it&rsquo;s certainly satisfying to order your car with the precise options you want.&nbsp; But a new car loses thousands of dollars of value the moment you bring it home.&nbsp; Take your time, do your homework and shop around.&nbsp; You&rsquo;ll be able to find a pre-owned car in great condition that can still&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">give your heart a thrill</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">.&nbsp; With the money you save, it&rsquo;ll be like getting free gas for a year!</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">2.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Diamonds.&nbsp; Why would anyone pay thousands for a diamond when today&rsquo;s &ldquo;fakes&rdquo; are so good?&nbsp; Only a gemologist with a loupe can distinguish a diamond from moissanite, a brilliant man-made stone.&nbsp; Unless you have gemologists in your social circle, save your cash for something with real value&mdash;perhaps a precious metals mutual fund.</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;When proposing, of course, stick with the real thing.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">3.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Department store clothes.&nbsp; There are far too many discount shops selling high-quality clothing for you to ever pay department store prices.&nbsp; Even better are consignment shops, where you&rsquo;ll likely find many designer items with the tags still attached.&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">If that&rsquo;s too much work and not enough glamour, try designer outlets.&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Sure, it may take a little more time to find exactly what you want, but you&rsquo;ll be able to buy a lot more clothes for a lot less money.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">4.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Books.&nbsp; Be honest.&nbsp; Are you ever going to re-read &ldquo;Anna Karenina&rdquo; or &ldquo;Lord of the Flies&rdquo;?&nbsp; Of course not.&nbsp; There are far too many good books still left to read for the first time.&nbsp; So why keep buying your own personal editions just to have them collect dust for years to come?&nbsp; If you read only two books a month, at $15 apiece, you could save $360 each year simply by taking them out of the library.&nbsp; Keep the cash and use it to pay for some of your kids&rsquo; college textbooks instead.</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;Plus, if you&rsquo;re not on a Kindle already, you&rsquo;ll be using an e-reader soon. And all those dusty volumes just mean you need to buy more bookshelves. If you truly can&rsquo;t resist, get used ones on Amazon.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">5.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Bottled water.&nbsp; Are you still paying for water?&nbsp; You&rsquo;ve heard the news that much of it comes from regular municipal water supplies, right?&nbsp; Even if your tap water isn&rsquo;t top-notch, you can buy a water filter for the tap for a fraction of what you&rsquo;re paying for the pricy plastic bottles.&nbsp; Save your money and donate it to charity:water, an organization that provides drinkable water to people who really need it.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1051,1575,1,'2010-02-20 01:24:30','2010-03-08 16:00:06',NULL),(22,30,'The Super Saver','<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; \"> </span><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><b><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"4\">Results:</font></b></font></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><b><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">The Super Saver:</font></b></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">You love to save money.&nbsp; You can&rsquo;t understand the mentality of buying a brand new Lexus when your 1988 Corolla is still running just fine.&nbsp; The store-brand bread tastes almost as good as the more expensive brands, and don&rsquo;t even get you started on five-dollar cups of coffee.&nbsp; You get satisfaction from saving money and have the healthy bank account to show for it.&nbsp; But there are some areas in life where it&rsquo;s worth it to spend more.&nbsp; Here are five:</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">1.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Grooming.&nbsp; You can get a hair cut at any inexpensive shop, but if you want to be taken seriously in the office, be willing to pay more at a better salon.&nbsp; A sophisticated cut (and color, if needed) can make a big difference in how other people perceive you and in how you feel about&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">y</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">oursel</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">f</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">.&nbsp; Don&rsquo;t forget well-manicured hands which convey an image of professionalism and self-respect.&nbsp; Yes, great grooming does cost more, but it really pays off in the workplace.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">2.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">A</font></font>&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">well-</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">tailored suit.&nbsp; Like grooming, a great suit can go a long way towards furthering your career goals.&nbsp; And the comfort of knowing that you have a perfectly tailored and flattering suit, one that can be used for interviews as well as weddings and other affairs, is well worth the initial outlay.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Select a classic style and color, so you&rsquo;ll get plenty of use out of it. And nobody will be able to tell that you bought it at a discount, so go for the consignment shops and outlets and find a thrilling bargain.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">3.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Entertainment.&nbsp; Life as Aesop&rsquo;s ant can get a little tiresome.&nbsp; Yes, you can stay home and&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">forgo cable</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">, but&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">you&rsquo;ll feel more reward if you get out and enjoy cultural opportunities</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">.&nbsp; Balance your frugal ways with regular splurges on true entertainment, whether it&rsquo;s subscribing to a concert series or going to a comedy club with friends.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">4.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Newspaper subscription.&nbsp; Newspapers around the country are folding as people get more of their news online, but too often online readers just skim the major headlines.&nbsp; Receiving a regular newspaper exposes you to a broader range of news, as well as entertainment offerings and coupons that can more than&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">compensate</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;for the cost of the paper.&nbsp; Any way you look at it, it&rsquo;s a great investment.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">5.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Gym membership.&nbsp; You can get your exercise from running around the neighborhood and doing push-ups in your living room, but are you actually&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">squeezing those workouts into your week</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">?&nbsp; Belonging to a gym provides health benefits, saving you money down the road</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;in terms of healthcare costs. And your resistance to waste will ensure you make good use of your membership.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><b>&nbsp;</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\"><b><br />\r\n</b></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',0,700,1,'2010-02-20 01:26:34','2010-03-08 16:00:28',NULL),(23,30,'Balanced Saver','<p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><b><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"4\">Results</font></b></font>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><b><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Balanced Saver&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></b></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Congratulations!&nbsp; You&rsquo;re the balanced saver.&nbsp; You set money aside for retirement, college tuition and the annual summer vacation.&nbsp; You take the money you saved by buying a second-hand car and pay down some mortgage principal.&nbsp; You&rsquo;re the definition of the sensible spender.&nbsp; But admit it&mdash;it gets a little boring being so sensible all the time.&nbsp; You might be missing out on some of the thrill that the Super Saver and the Easy Spender enjoy.&nbsp; Here are five ideas for some frivolity that won&rsquo;t break the bank:</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">1.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">A massage.&nbsp; Massages don&rsquo;t have to cost much money, but they sure can make you feel pampered.&nbsp; Try contacting a massage school to see if their students give&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">reduced</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">-rate&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">sessions</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">.</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;There are a lot of health benefits from stress reduction, so it&rsquo;s worth the splurge.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">2.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">A weekend cruise.&nbsp; Act the part of the socialite and book a spur-of-the-moment cruise.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Last-minute, o</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">ff-season cruises for three or four days are remarkably inexpensive, but you can cram a lot of enjoyment into that time.&nbsp; With meals and most entertainment included, you won&rsquo;t have to worry that you&rsquo;re blowing through your budget.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">3.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">A personal shopper.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">When your wardrobe needs a bit of an update, g</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">ive yourself a budget for the day and make an appointment with a department store&rsquo;s personal shopper. While you wouldn&rsquo;t want to pay department store prices every time you shop, taking advantage of a personal shopper&rsquo;s style expertise can pay big dividends the next time you go shopping solo.&nbsp; And what could be more spoiled than sitting in a dressing room waiting for someone to bring you more clothes to try on?</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">4.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Go to the movies.&nbsp; Not all guilty pleasures have to be costly.&nbsp; Go with a friend to a midweek matinee, something that your spouse or kids probably won&rsquo;t want to see.&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">(Yes, you can take a mental health day from work every so often.)</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;The theater will be largely empty, a reminder that other people are hard at work while you&rsquo;re kicking back with a bucket of popcorn.&nbsp; It&rsquo;s a wonderfully decadent experience.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">5.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Buy yourself roses.&nbsp; Why wait for a special occasion to bring beautiful fresh flowers in the house?&nbsp; Pick up a dozen roses and set the vase where you can enjoy them all the time.&nbsp;</font></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">No, you won&rsquo;t do it often, but when you do invest in this little treat, you&rsquo;ll smile every time you see them. That&rsquo;s well worth it.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',701,1050,1,'2010-02-20 01:27:31','2010-03-08 16:00:43',NULL),(24,31,'You jump at the chance to work out','<p><b>You\'re an Eager Beaver Exerciser</b></p>\r\n<p>You jump at any chance to exercise and love the opportunity to add variety to your routine and learn new skills.  Your enthusiasm can be infectious.  You can even go a little overboard with your commitment to the gym, which can cause some tension in your relationships, particularly with people who aren&rsquo;t as interested in physical activity.   You could try to round out your understanding of health to include the mental side.  Good activities to try:</p>\r\n<p>1. Kripalu yoga.  Some forms of yoga are so strenuous it&rsquo;s hard to stay focused on your breathing and mental state.  In Kripalu yoga, the poses are held for a longer time, and you&rsquo;ll walk away feeling both limber and serene.</p>\r\n<p>2. Fencing.  You might think this sport is just for the upper crust, but it provides a great all-over toning and cardio workout.  Instead of mindless repetition on an elliptical trainer, though, in fencing you will need to maintain a high level of mental alertness coupled with calm. Think of it as an energetic chess game.</p>\r\n<p>3. Tai Chi.  Just as Americans hit the pavement for an early morning jog, large numbers of people perform Tai Chi in parks in China.  This ancient Chinese exercise involves slow, fluid movements matched to your breathing, promoting a sense of well-being and calm.</p>',1550,1800,1,'2010-02-20 03:25:25','2010-10-17 15:58:48',NULL),(25,31,'You are a Tried and True Exerciser','<p><b>You make time for the exercise exhilaration</b></p>\r\n<p>You know the statistics about heart health, and you know that regular physical activity is key for a long and healthy life.  You make time for it regularly, no matter what else is on your schedule.  But you can fall into a routine and miss out on the exhilaration of exercising for its own sake, rather than for its longer-term benefits.  Adding some variety to your routine would help shake you out of your rut.  Activities to try:</p>\r\n<p>1.    Ice skating.   Few activities compare to the thrill of zipping around the ice.  Once you master the basics of stopping and crossover turns, you can confidently build up speed and get a great workout.  You can skate on your own, or take lessons in figure skating or speed skating or try ice hockey when your skills on skates are up to the challenge.  With the cold air, the slick speed and the promise of a hot chocolate, you&rsquo;ll feel like you&rsquo;re a kid again.</p>\r\n<p>2.    Tennis doubles.  It doesn&rsquo;t take many lessons to be able to sustain a decent tennis rally.  Once you can keep a ball in play, find an athletic facility that offers tennis round robins.  Many facilities will allow you to play even as a non-member.  Doubles is a fast-paced and social activity, requiring quick reflexes and good teamwork.  During the summer, you can usually play outdoors for free!</p>\r\n<p>3.    Dancing.  Some forms of dancing are quite rigorous, right from the start.  Find a style that appeals to you; jazz, hip-hop, tap and ballet can all provide a great workout.  But you&rsquo;ll be having so much fun; you won&rsquo;t even realize that you&rsquo;re exercising.</p>',1191,1549,1,'2010-02-20 03:27:01','2010-10-17 15:59:10',NULL),(26,31,'You may be missing out and we’ve got ideas','<p><b>You\'re an Easy-Does-It Exerciser</b></p>\r\n<p>When it comes to exercise, your attitude is easy-does-it.  You enjoy light-to-moderate physical activity.  Although you&rsquo;re often game to try a new sport, you don&rsquo;t commit yourself to improving at it.  While it&rsquo;s good to not be fanatical about exercise, you may not be getting enough physical benefit from your routine.  And you may be missing out on some of the mental rewards that come from mastering a new sport and getting healthier.  Some activities you might want to try:</p>\r\n<p>1. Personal training.  Time with a trainer can be a great investment.  Not only can a trainer design a program for long-term improvement, she can encourage you to push yourself harder than you thought you could go.  You may even find some of your trainer&rsquo;s commitment and passion for exercise rubbing off on you.</p>\r\n<p>2.  Running clubs.  Running clubs are an easy, inexpensive way of getting some inspiration and motivation.  Knowing that everyone in your group is working for a goal can give you an exercise focus that you didn&rsquo;t have before.  Better yet, sign up with a fellow runner for an upcoming 5K; for extra motivation, run for a charitable cause.</p>\r\n<p>3.  Intramural soccer leagues.  Soccer isn&rsquo;t a difficult sport to learn, and you&rsquo;ll bolster your confidence and self-esteem as you learn new skills.  There&rsquo;s plenty of running, plus great team camaraderie to help push you harder.</p>',800,1190,1,'2010-02-20 03:29:22','2010-10-17 16:00:31',NULL),(27,32,'The Hands-on Volunteer','<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; \"> </span></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"font-size: 18pt; margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><b><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"4\">Results:&nbsp;</font></b></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">The Hands-on Volunteer</font></font></h1>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">The personal connection is important to you when it comes to volunteering.&nbsp; You want to know the people you are helping, both to show them someone cares and to broaden your own experience.&nbsp; Many organizations are in need of just that personal touch.&nbsp; Consider volunteering your time for one of these four worthy causes:</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">1.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Meals-on-Wheels - Meals-on-Wheels keeps rolling along, decades after its first meals were delivered to shut-ins in Philadelphia.&nbsp; If you have just a little time to spare, but would like to make that personal connection to someone in need, Meals-on-Wheels could use your services.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 18pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">2.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Big Brother/Big Sister - Mentoring a young person may sound like a difficult task, but it shouldn&rsquo;t be.&nbsp; Get together with your &ldquo;little sibling&rdquo; once or twice a week to go skating or eat pizza, and be a supportive friend.&nbsp; It can make a world of difference in the life of a troubled child.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">3.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">A soup kitchen - Soup kitchens serve more than soup, and they need volunteers to do it.&nbsp; You don&rsquo;t need to be a gourmet chef, you just need to be able to commit to a schedule.&nbsp; You&rsquo;ll never be so grateful to have a home.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">4.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Animal shelter - If you&rsquo;re an animal lover, working at a shelter can provide immeasurable rewards for both the animals and you.&nbsp; Cleaning cages, socializing kittens and walking dogs are all services animal shelters need.&nbsp; Visit the ASPCA&rsquo;s website to find animal shelters near you.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',0,700,1,'2010-02-20 19:06:36','2010-03-08 15:44:21',NULL),(28,32,'The Big Splash','<p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\', Verdana, sans-serif\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; \"> </span></span></font></p>\r\n<p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\', Verdana, sans-serif\"> </font></p>\r\n<p><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\', Verdana, sans-serif\">\r\n<h1 style=\"font-size: 18pt; margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><b><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"4\">Results:&nbsp;</font></b></font><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">The Big Splash</font></font></h1>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">You know organizations can&rsquo;t get much done with cash, both for direct giving and for its own operational costs.&nbsp; You find satisfaction in raising the funds for organizations, and like seeing the impressive totals raised during walk-a-thons and silent auctions.&nbsp; You also enjoy the emotional rush that comes from being part of a large event.&nbsp; Try one of these four charities when you want to make a big splash:</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">1.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Special Olympics - Help the Special Olympics in your area at its athletic events, Serve as a timekeeper, cheer from the stands or help officiate.&nbsp; You&rsquo;ll be feeling great about yourself as you help pull together a big event in the lives of these talented athletes.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">2.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Make-a-Wish Foundation - Just the idea of granting a wish to a seriously ill child is enough to bring a smile to anyone&rsquo;s face.&nbsp; Help Make-a-Wish raise the funds to make a child&rsquo;s dream come true.&nbsp;</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">3.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Relay for Life - The American Cancer Society&rsquo;s fundraising event, the Relay for Life gathers groups of people in parks across the country for relay-style walks and runs, typically lasting for 24 hours.&nbsp; Each year, millions of people participate.&nbsp; If you or someone you know has battled cancer, this inspiring community event may be a good choice for you.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">4.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Salvation Army - Doing good around the world doesn&rsquo;t come cheap, particularly when you have to travel to get there.&nbsp; If you&rsquo;re feeling extra generous, consider donating your United Airlines frequent flier miles to the Salvation Army.&nbsp; The joint program, in existence since 1999, has helped send medical personnel where it&rsquo;s needed, including to Ground Zero.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \">&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n</font></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',701,1050,1,'2010-02-20 19:08:22','2010-03-08 15:44:40',NULL),(29,32,'Policy Work','<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; \"> </span></p>\r\n<h1 style=\"font-size: 18pt; margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><b><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"4\">Results:</font></b></font>&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Policy Work</font></font></h1>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">As satisfying as working with individuals can be, you see the need to try to affect the decision makers&mdash;congressmen, state representatives, United Nations officials.&nbsp; Swaying the minds of the people who write the laws and control the money may be a slow process and short on immediate rewards.&nbsp; But when change happens, many people benefit, and you get the reward of an enormous victory.&nbsp; One of these causes may be just the fit for you:</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 18pt; \">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">1.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">WWF - The Conservation Action Network of WWF provides you with letters to send to your government representatives on a host of ecological issues.&nbsp; Just a short investment of time can have a big impact, and you&rsquo;ll keep up to date with the latest battles in conservation.</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">2.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Mothers Against Drunk Driving - Thirty years after its founding, MADD is still going strong, working on anti-drunk driving initiatives throughout the country, such as ignition interlocks for convicted drunk driving offenders.&nbsp;</font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=\"\'times new roman\'\"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">3.</font></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<font class=\"Apple-style-span\" face=