 through the sports you watch. Winning is everything.</p>\r\n<p>Top 10 Ways to Drop $250 Feeding Your Need for Competition</p>\r\n<p>1.    A ticket to Game Seven of the World Series, even if it is in the nosebleed section.</p>\r\n<p>2.    A used Xbox 360, to exorcise your demons.</p>\r\n<p>3.    An Everlast punching bag, with enough extra cash to buy the Rocky soundtrack.</p>\r\n<p>4.    A new Taylor Made driver, to get 20 extra yards off the tee against your golfing buddies.</p>\r\n<p>5.    ESPN Classic, where the cash gets spread out but is the gift that keeps on giving.</p>\r\n<p>6.    DirecTV&rsquo;s &ldquo;Sunday Ticket,&rdquo; giving you every NFL game.</p>\r\n<p>7.    Tickets to Game Seven of any NBA playoff series.</p>\r\n<p>8.    A plane ticket to see Lance Armstrong ride during a stateside time trial.</p>\r\n<p>9.    City league basketball or softball fees, for the weekly dose of competition.</p>\r\n<p>10.  Fantasy league dues, to dominate your co-workers and friends.</p>',800,1200,1,'2010-02-20 21:59:27','2010-10-19 17:29:55',NULL),(34,34,'You are a fan of sports tradition','<p><b>You are a sportsman</b></p>\r\n<p>As a fan of tradition, you know the outcome matters, but so does the process. Winning and good theater are inherently married together. You can&rsquo;t stand cheaters or anyone who throws in the towel before giving their all.</p>\r\n<p>Top 10 Ways to Spend $250 Being a Good Sport</p>\r\n<p>1.    Tickets for Opening Day, as long as it is your favorite baseball team.</p>\r\n<p>2.    Green fees at Spyglass, since Pebble Beach is still too expensive ($425).</p>\r\n<p>3.    A game-worn jersey of your favorite player (to frame, not to wear).</p>\r\n<p>4.    Tickets to the Kentucky Derby, even if just once.</p>\r\n<p>5.    The MLB season pass, giving you access to your favorite team all season.</p>\r\n<p>6.    Tickets to a Packers-Bears game at Lambeau Field.</p>\r\n<p>7.    DVD championship set for your favorite team&rsquo;s title, for the down years.</p>\r\n<p>8.    A complete set of baseball cards from the year you graduated high school.</p>\r\n<p>9.    Subscriptions to the best sports magazines and papers, restoring a lost joy.</p>\r\n<p>10.  March Madness office pools, and maybe even taking in a local game.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1201,1400,1,'2010-02-20 22:00:08','2010-10-17 16:01:52',NULL),(35,34,'You love the spectacle of sports','<p><b>You&rsquo;re a fan of the game</b></p>\r\n<p>As a lover of show, the style and celebrity of the event matter more than who wins. Entertainment value is what draws you to buy tickets or tune in.</p>\r\n<p>Top 10 Ways to Invest $250 Enjoying the Pageantry</p>\r\n<p>1.    Tickets to the NBA All-Star Game, preferably for the dunk contest.</p>\r\n<p>2.    DVD copies of every great sports movie you can think of.</p>\r\n<p>3.    Red Sox-Yankees tickets, regardless of the game.</p>\r\n<p>4.    Bleacher seats at Wrigley Field, regardless of the opponent.</p>\r\n<p>5.    Nosebleed seats for the Super Bowl, as long as it is in Miami.</p>\r\n<p>6.    Passes to take your kids to the &ldquo;Meet the Team&rdquo; day during the preseason.</p>\r\n<p>7.    Tickets to the NBA or NFL Draft, at Madison Square Garden.</p>\r\n<p>8.    Tickets to an exhibition game for Team USA Basketball.</p>\r\n<p>9.    Pay-per-view costs for the year&rsquo;s big boxing matches.</p>\r\n<p>10.   A gambling stash, for the next time you go to Vegas.</p>',1401,1800,1,'2010-02-20 22:00:46','2010-10-17 16:02:17',NULL),(36,35,'Quiz Recommendation','',0,1e+06,1,'2010-04-19 02:55:15','2010-04-19 02:55:15',NULL),(37,36,'You\'re a Search and Wait job Seeker','<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; \">\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Results:&nbsp;</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">You</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&rsquo;re a</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;Search and</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;Wait Job Seeker</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">:</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">When it comes to your job search your attitude is, something will happen eventually.&nbsp; You spend 1 hour a day looking for work.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">It&rsquo;s time to put some basic advice to work.&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Some options for you are:</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">1.</font></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Learn about networking websites</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;to meet people.&nbsp; Almost 80% of jobs are obtained through networking.&nbsp; Use that to your advantage.</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">2.</font></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Go to a job fair and practice interviewing</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">.&nbsp; Practice makes perfect and it also can provide an opportunity for you to get feedback from professionals.</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">3.</font></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Revise&nbsp;</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">your&nbsp;</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">resume and have&nbsp;</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">it&nbsp;</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">ready to send out&nbsp;</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">for appropriate jobs</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">.</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp; Often it helps to customize your resume for different jobs, but be sure to keep track of what you sent to whom.</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">4.</font></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Always use a cover letter.&nbsp; Just sending a resume shows a lack of focus on the particular opportunity.&nbsp; Make them know you are excited.</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n</span></p>',0,1000,1,'2010-06-24 00:53:27','2010-06-24 00:53:27',NULL),(38,36,'You\'re a Moderate Job Seeker','<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; \">\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">You&rsquo;re&nbsp;</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">a Moderate Job Seeker</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">When it comes to your job search, your attitude is</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;it will happen if I just work keep looking.&nbsp; This is good as you are proactive in your search, and spending&nbsp;</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">3-4 hours a day looking for work&nbsp;</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">should help you</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;find a job eventually. Some options for you are:</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">1.</font></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">S</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">etting up job alerts on indeed.</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">com</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;and s</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">earching job listings on monster.com</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">2.</font></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Take a class</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">es</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;and learn a new skill&nbsp;</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">to bolster your credentials</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">3.</font></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Don&rsquo;t be concerned if</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;a few weeks go by without an interview.&nbsp; Don&rsquo;t give up!&nbsp; Job opportunities always tend to come in streaks.</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">4.</font></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Don&rsquo;t just send our resumes and cover letters; you MUST also follow up with every job lead.&nbsp; Use the phone and use email.</font></span></p>\r\n</span></p>',1001,1500,1,'2010-06-24 00:54:23','2010-06-24 00:54:23',NULL),(39,36,'You\'re an Aggressive Job Seeker','<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; \">\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">You</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&rsquo;re</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;an Aggressive Job Seeker:</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">When it comes to your job search, you are on top of your game.&nbsp; You contact all your friends and family and old work colleagues to see if they can help you find a job. You are contacting people on all the top networking sites.&nbsp; Some options for you are:</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">1.</font></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Connect</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;wi</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">th old work colleagues through Linked I</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">n</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">.</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp; Online social networks can be a great way to find the &ldquo;hard to find&rdquo; opportunities.</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">2.</font></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Have multiple resumes developed and cater resumes for different job listings</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">.</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp; Be sure to keep track of which resume is sent to whom so as to avoid appearing disorganized.</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">3.</font></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Maintaining and following up with your contacts after</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;your</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;job interviews.</font></span><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp; Often one interview can lead to the identification of other opportunities.</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 36pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">4.</font></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">Don&rsquo;t take the first job you get unless it&rsquo;s right for you and takes you where you want to go.&nbsp; Your approach and attitude are right on target &ndash; opportunities will come.&nbsp; Be sure to make sure the one is right.</font></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-right: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0pt; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><font class=\"Apple-style-span\" size=\"3\">&nbsp;</font></span></p>\r\n<div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: medium;\"><br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n</span></div>',1501,2250,1,'2010-06-24 00:55:05','2010-06-24 00:55:16',NULL),(40,37,'It’s traditional love for you','<p><b>Strict &ndash; It&rsquo;s your way or the highway</b></p>\r\n<p>You are quite conservative when it comes to dating, and it&rsquo;s clear you take the more traditional route when it comes to love. So traditional, in fact, that it&rsquo;s more &ldquo;old school&rdquo; &ndash; as in Old World &ndash; than modern times permit. There is nothing wrong with holding on to traditional values, but it&rsquo;s okay to seek out men who share your value system in non-traditional venues, such as online dating web sites or speed-dating events at your local house of worship. If it&rsquo;s parental disapproval you are fearing, have a heart-to-heart talk with your mom and dad, perhaps getting a trusted aunt or brother and sister in your court first. Make it clear that, while you respect them and their traditions, you are an adult who has to make her own way in life, and that includes picking a mate.</p>',751,1250,1,'2010-06-25 00:05:47','2010-10-17 16:03:18',NULL),(41,37,'You move away from the comfort zone and get better with time','<p><b>You like a little adventure</b></p>\r\n<p>You like being a little more adventurous and move away from your comfort zone when seeking individuals who share your beliefs. With a balanced approach to dating, you are far more likely to find the man of your dreams rather than suffer through too many nightmarish dates.  Continue to expand your opportunities to meet new people, whether it&rsquo;s through volunteer work or taking evening classes for adults. Even if you don&rsquo;t meet the perfect mate, you will be helping people and learning new skills, which are invaluable. Remember, you&rsquo;ll kiss a lot of frogs before you find that one prince, but once the magic happens, it may just mean a lifetime of happiness.</p>',1251,1850,1,'2010-06-25 00:09:18','2010-10-17 16:03:29',NULL),(42,37,'Slow down to find true love','<p><b>Anything Goes Dater</b></p>\r\n<p>Slow down, sister! Walking too much on the wild side of town is fun for the moment, but those moments are fleeting, and if you are serious about finding a mate &ndash; or going on a serious date &ndash; you need to realize that downing shots is drowning your chances for finding true love. If you want to change your success rate, change your environment. Stay away from loud, crowded bars and spend more time networking with friends and family to help you on your search.  If you have any hobbies, like sports or collecting, join some local groups so you will immediately have one thing in common with other singles in the club. Consider volunteering your time at a local charity. It is a great way to meet people who have strong values and are generous with their time. This is about sending you down the right path towards finding true love rather than stopping at all the honkytonks along the way.</p>',1851,2250,1,'2010-06-25 00:10:50','2010-10-17 16:03:51',NULL),(43,37,'You approach all things sensibly, but you can find more','<p><b>You are Sensible, Safe and Pragmatic</b></p>\r\n<p>You have a sensible approach to life and how and when to spend your time. You are busy working at the same job for many years with a stable income.  At night you go home but occasionally stay after work to go to a local bar to hang out with your co-workers. Consider joining a local book club to expand your personal relationships and find a new favorite author. Let your friends -- both married and single &ndash; know that you still feel they are important to you in your life and you don\'t want too much time to go by without seeing them.  You never know when they may have a single friend for you to meet.</p>',500,750,1,'2010-06-25 00:12:06','2010-10-17 16:04:03',NULL),(44,38,'You are indifferent about shopping','<p><b>You are a Necessity Shopper</b></p>\r\n<p>You are indifferent about shopping. You tend to go to stores only when you absolutely need something, and you are just as happy to make do with what you have. You have hobbies and interests that take up much of your free time, and spending time with loved ones is important to you. Spending your money on more &ldquo;stuff&rdquo; doesn&rsquo;t appeal to you.  You are focused and efficient with your money and your time.  When you \'absolutely need something, you buy something.\'</p>',1875,2250,1,'2010-06-25 02:28:24','2010-10-17 16:04:55',NULL),(45,38,'You are a Casual Shopper','<p><b>You shop occasionally</b></p>\r\n<p>While you appreciate new things and interesting finds, you wouldn&rsquo;t go out of your way or change any social plans just to go shopping. You have a busy social life full of interesting activities and you are able to balance your time and money by not going crazy at the mall.  When you go to lunch with your friends on Main Street, you park far away from the restaurant leaving time to window shop.</p>',1251,1874,1,'2010-06-25 02:30:07','2010-11-24 17:17:35',NULL),(46,38,'You are a Shopaholic','<p><b>You absolutely love to shop</b></p>\r\n<p>You may be a shopaholic! Do you find yourself canceling plans with friends because there&rsquo;s a sale at your favorite department store? Are you finding it hard to make the minimum payments on your credit cards each month? Shopping is fun, and having new clothing and housewares is great, but you have to ask yourself if you&rsquo;re shopping for the right reasons. Maybe you&rsquo;re bored. Consider joining a local social group in your town to meet new people and cultivate new hobbies. Try to increase your exercise levels. For some people, acquiring new items raises their spirits; exercise can produce that same release of endorphins responsible for the &ldquo;rush.&rdquo; Quitting shopping cold turkey can be impossible for some people, but here is an idea to try. If you see something you must have, make yourself wait a day. Ask the store if they can put it on hold for you. Go home and sleep on it. If you absolutely still want the item the next day, return to the store and buy it. This &ldquo;slowing down&rdquo; will force you to put more thought into your purchases.</p>',1000,1250,1,'2010-06-25 02:32:25','2010-11-24 17:18:25',NULL),(47,38,'You are an Online Shopper','<p><b>You\'re online all the time</b></p>\r\n<p>You\'ve embraced the technology of the new millennium -- well, at least as far as shopping is concerned. No longer a slave to crowded mall parking lots, you consider shipping costs more reasonable than paying for gas and tolls to get to the shopping center. You\'ve even tried a shop-at-home grocery website, though you think they need to work out a few more kinks in their produce and frozen foods delivery. You love coming home from work to see what the mailman has dropped off for you. Since you\'ve discovered trying on clothing purchases in the comfort of your own home, you avoid stores as much as possible nowadays.</p>',2251,3000,1,'2010-06-25 02:34:02','2010-11-24 17:19:46',NULL),(48,39,'Visit more of America and expand your horizons','<p><b>You are a Domestic Traveler</b></p>\r\n<p>You love what America has to offer and welcome the opportunity to explore new vistas or routes you\'ve never seen before. But don\'t miss out on exciting things to see and do in your own town. You may make new friends in the process and appreciate what\'s going on in your own backyard. Also, don\'t be afraid to research a foreign country you\'ve read about but never dreamed you\'d see in person. You may find that you\'re more of an intrepid traveler than you thought!</p>',1351,1700,1,'2010-06-25 03:31:45','2010-10-17 15:51:13',NULL),(49,39,'The joys of travel are just a few steps from your home','<p><b>You are a Local Traveler</b></p>\r\n<p>Your dream vacation finds you only steps away from home. You enjoy what your region has to offer and you rarely seek out the unfamiliar. While this probably makes for stress-free trip planning, you should consider trying something different once in a while. Whether it\'s getting on a plane and visiting a romantic city like Paris, or driving cross country to check out a national park you read about in school, expanding your travel horizons could give you countless benefits... and memories to last a lifetime!</p>',1000,1350,1,'2010-06-25 03:32:28','2010-10-17 15:51:26',NULL),(50,39,'You crave adventure and dream vacations','<p><b>You are a World Traveler</b></p>\r\n<p>You crave adventure and want your dreams to become your vacation realities. You\'re not satisfied with ordinary experiences and live life to the fullest through your travel destinations. But don\'t forget about all your own country has to offer. With 50 states to choose from, there is no end to what you can see and do in the United States. In addition, don\'t write off a &quot;staycation&quot; just yet. In addition to saving money, you will be helping your local businesses and economy by spending vacation dollars close to home. It will give you a new appreciation for what\'s going on in your own backyard.</p>',1701,2250,1,'2010-06-25 03:34:50','2010-10-17 15:51:45',NULL),(51,40,'You are like Tobey Maguire and Helen Mirren','<p><b>You Prefer to Fly Under the Radar</b></p>\r\n<p>You are most like Tobey Maguire, Sean Penn, Jennifer Garner and Helen Mirren wrapped up into one.</p>\r\n<p>When not filming or promoting a blockbuster movie, you rarely appear in the public eye or press. Your identity as a celebrity is tied only to your performances.  You prefer to lead a quiet life with your family and react adversely to the intrusion of photographers.   All in all, you tend to fly under the radar and raise little controversy.</p>\r\n<p>When pushed, you are fiercely private about your personal life and may become aggressive in your defense of it.  You tend to lash out when your space is invaded.  However, despite holding a close hand concerning your life behind the scenes, you tend to be quite outspoken about your political and/or social interests.   A fine line is drawn&mdash;one often only clear to you--between the personal and the political.</p>\r\n<p>Though recognized everywhere you go, you generally avoid the press unless promoting a movie or appearing on the red carpet with your significant other.   You strive to maintain your privacy and live a normal life, despite the hounding of photographers.  Selling your personal photos to magazines or tabloids is not an option.  Sometimes the paparazzi get too close, but you keep your poise and avoid confrontation.</p>\r\n<p>In the end you always show up at an awards show prepared and ready to take the best actor award home with you.   The roles you prefer are period pieces where your character transforms back to another era, time and dress.</p>',1301,2250,1,'2010-06-25 10:30:36','2010-10-17 16:15:28',NULL),(52,40,'You are Meryl Streep and Ed Norton','<p>You occasionally exploit the perks, but would keep your ego in check!  You are Meryl Streep, Jennifer Lopez and Ed Norton rolled into one.</p>\r\n<p>A diva, you yearn to be a singular act at all times.  Instead of interviews, you primarily express yourself through fashion, flawless make-up and hair.  Rumors occasionally proliferate in the tabloids, but you rarely provide a response or acknowledgment.  Your interviews and photos come at a price &ndash; the sale of your wedding and baby photos to popular magazines and tabloids draws top dollar.  Overall, you prefer the glamour to the gossip.  Your style is your brand.</p>\r\n<p>When you take on a role, you are a chameleon. The way you transform the various characters you portray, you completely nail them all, leaving the audience breathless.  You are a good role model for young up and coming actors to follow by honing your craft to the max!  None of the other actors want to be up against you in the best actress category because there is no chance.  They are still honored to be in the same category as you and in your presence.</p>\r\n<p>In the end, you are the new generation of talent following in the footsteps of the great actors of all time and have starred in numerous Hollywood blockbusters.  You lead a low key life and do interviews and talk shows when you are hyping a new film. The paparazzi does not focus on your social life and you stay away from Twitter, Facebook and MySpace and don&rsquo;t understand why someone would want to be tracked down 24 hours a day.</p>',851,1300,1,'2010-06-25 10:31:43','2010-10-17 16:18:37',NULL),(53,40,'In your next life you will be Beyonce Knowles or Sasha Baron Cohen','<p>You want as much celebrity as possible and will take every advantage that comes with it.  You are Paris Hilton, Beyonce Knowles, Madonna and Sasha Baron Cohen rolled into one.</p>\r\n<p>You crave attention and will do nearly anything to get it.  Not only is every activity a photo-op, you call the paparazzi in advance to tell them where you&rsquo;ll be.  You love to be &ldquo;caught out shopping&rdquo; on Robertson and Rodeo, lunching at the latest LA hotspot, on the beach in the Riviera and/or posing at the latest designer boutique opening.  You are not a stranger to embarrassing publicity, but have learned that any and all press is good press.  Some might find you to be self-centered and high maintenance, but you know they&rsquo;re just jealous.</p>\r\n<p>Luckily, you were born to be a star and take full advantage of the perks.  You aim to rule over a boundless empire:  gold records, endorsements, commercials, an Oscar, a designer clothing line; you want it all.  Over-exposure is not part of your lexicon.  Bring the fame and bring the noise.</p>\r\n<p>You are purposeful and premeditated in your pursuit of press and notoriety.   You constantly reinvent yourself in order to keep the public&rsquo;s interest.  You do not shy away from controversy and, frequently, seek it out.  You are unapologetic about your choices and do it your own way. Never one to be owned or told what to do, you have created the ultimate brand:  yourself.</p>\r\n<p>To stay in the spotlight, you will do any stunts to shock your audience, so being in front of the paparazzi in pursuit of a good picture and crazy story that sells to all the tabloids is your main goal.  You look forward to the most publicity and subsequent lawsuits.   You are currently brainstorming your next MTV type stunt when you are finished with your latest documentary.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',700,850,1,'2010-06-25 10:33:08','2010-10-17 16:21:28',NULL),(54,41,'You have the right combination of excitement and life','<p><b>You\'re a Balanced Board</b></p>\r\n<p>You are a Balance Board, trying to find the right combination between a little excitement and not too exciting as to throw your whole day out of whack. Staying in the middle of the scale is never easy and it&rsquo;s O.K. to let that needle swing a little hard in either direction once in a while.</p>',1251,1750,1,'2010-06-26 01:49:29','2010-10-17 16:59:07',NULL),(55,41,'You are burning the candle at both ends ','<p><b>You are a Little Firecracker</b></p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;re a Little Firecracker, burning both ends of the candle until the light goes out and there&rsquo;s nothing left. Every battery needs a recharge, so don&rsquo;t be afraid to slow the pace &ndash; even for a day &ndash; and embrace life without hugging it to death.</p>',1751,2250,1,'2010-06-26 01:50:17','2010-10-17 17:00:32',NULL),(56,42,'Everybody loves Raymond but you are Debra Barone – the woman behind it all','<p><b>You are Debra Barone</b></p>\r\n<p>Everybody may love Raymond, but it&rsquo;s you &ndash; Debra Barone &ndash; who deserves all the credit. You&rsquo;re a stay-at-home mom who can make three different kinds of PB&amp;J sandwiches with one hand, while holding a crying baby in the other. Like Annie Camden on &quot;Seventh Heaven,&quot; you have made sacrifices to stay home with your kids, but you know how quickly this time goes and you want to savor it. You have all of the responsibility, but get none of the fame&hellip;and you love every moment of it.</p>',1000,1250,1,'2010-06-26 01:57:45','2010-10-17 17:15:13',NULL),(57,42,'You are Claire Huxtable, balanced in every way','<p><b>You are Claire Huxtable</b></p>\r\n<p>You don\'t need a &quot;cliff&quot; to jump off, because it\'s you - Claire Huxtable - who can manage to keep career climbing without falling down on the job. Just like Maggie Seaver on &quot;Growing Pains&quot;, you have found a perfect balance between meeting your family\'s needs while climbing the corporate ladder. Your Smartphone is your best friend, and you\'ve managed your family affairs as well as any deal you&rsquo;ve closed.</p>',1251,1875,1,'2010-06-26 01:59:45','2010-10-17 17:16:47',NULL),(58,42,'It’s your world Murphy Brown and you’ve done it on your own','<p><b>You are Murphy Brown</b></p>\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s your world, Murphy Brown, and  you are happy to report you&rsquo;ve managed well on your own. Just like Angela Bower, you\'re &quot;the boss&quot; both at home and at work. Though you may not have a male nanny like Tony or sing in a band with your kids like Shirley on the &quot;Partridge Family,&quot; you&rsquo;re redefining the traditional family, and finding out that being independent isn&rsquo;t so bad.</p>',1876,2625,1,'2010-06-26 02:00:47','2010-10-17 17:18:12',NULL),(59,42,'Here’s the story of a lovely lady – You, Carol Brady','<p><b>You Are Carol Brady</b></p>\r\n<p>Here\'s the story of a lovely lady... and it\'s you! Your life has changed a lot! You\'re now a stay-at-home mom to a blended family, the result of marrying a man with kids after your divorce or being widowed. Your house has gotten much louder! But you are reveling in your family life. You\'re managing the needs of many kids with a wide age range, some still young and some growing into adulthood. You like being at home, managing the kids\' day-to-day schedules and refereeing the occasional disagreement that comes from sibling rivalry. While most of your neighbors have both parents working, you feel no pressure to do so, as the kids keep you so busy and you think it gives them some stability in this new living situation.</p>',2626,3000,1,'2010-06-26 02:01:48','2010-10-17 17:19:31',NULL),(60,41,'Your natural tranquility is infectious','<p><b>You\'re a Yoga Master</b></p>\r\n<p>All bow down to the yoga master! Your natural tranquility is infectious, and nothing can disrupt your utopian lifestyle. However, even in a perfect world, a little imperfection is a good thing, so find time here and there to get that heart and your chakras open a little more.</p>',1000,1250,1,'2010-07-01 22:49:44','2010-10-20 12:13:27',NULL),(1004,2,'Fair','<p>You have suffered or neglected your spiritual wellbeing, but the good news is that brighter days are ahead. Taking some simple steps are likely to propel you toward a more satisfying spiritual life, leading to better health and wellbeing, peace and comfort. </p>\r\n<p>Start with easy ways to bring meaning to your life by opening up to friends and family, carving out time to interact with others in a meaningful way. Listen to music and read literature that resonates with your sense of purpose. Select a living thing to nurture, and revel in the joy of watching it develop.</p>\r\n<p>Your Personalized Plan includes many more simple, sustainable steps you can take today to find joy in life. It also includes changes to implement over the coming weeks and months that deliver larger benefits. To receive your Personalized Plan, join the MaxWell Daily Club. As a member, you&rsquo;ll also get helpful interactive tools, one-on-one coaching, invitations to exclusive events, discounts, and more.</p>',800,999,1,'2008-10-15 21:58:55','2009-02-06 00:28:03',NULL),(1005,2,'Good','<p>You live a life that has significance, but a stronger spiritual connection could bring you more joy. Clearly, several of your habits are working well, and the task now is to identify the areas that are out of balance and take initial steps to find better health and wellbeing, peace and comfort.</p>\r\n<p>Bring more meaning to your life by identifying relationships to cultivate in a meaningful way. Find opportunities that resonate with your sense of purpose. Select a living thing to nurture, and revel in the miracle of watching it develop.</p>\r\n<p>Your Personalized Plan includes many more simple, sustainable steps you can take today enhance your spiritual life. It also includes changes to implement over the coming weeks and months that deliver larger benefits. To receive your Personalized Plan, join the MaxWell Daily Club. As a member, you&rsquo;ll also get helpful interactive tools, one-on-one coaching, invitations to exclusive events, discounts, and more.</p>',1000,1399,1,'2008-10-15 21:59:24','2009-02-06 00:29:32',NULL),(1006,2,'Excellent','<p>You have developed a strong spiritual engagement and experience in your life. The rewards are apparent in your sense of calmness and appreciation for the richness of your interactions and intimacy. Remain mindful of the shifts in your sense of comfort and peace that can come as a result of events close to home or even those halfway around the world. And never cease exploring new ways to enhance your sense of enlightenment. There is always a new idea or perspective that can expand your understanding and compassion.</p>\r\n<p>Your Personalized Plan offers a variety of suggestions to broaden your horizons toward increased peace and kindness. Join the MaxWell Daily Club for access to helpful interactive tools, one-on-one coaching, invitations to exclusive events, discounts, and more. </p>',1400,1600,1,'2008-10-15 22:02:15','2009-02-06 00:29:14',NULL),(1007,3,'Excellent','<p>Based on your responses to the preceding questions, your emotional state appears to be EXCELLENT! This is a very good place to be, but you realize you might be even better. Clearly,